      "id": "summary:abstract",
      "type": "abstract",
      "value": "Varnhagen briefly reviews nineteenth-century prints of The Thrush and the Nightingale and then transcribes from the Auchinleck manuscript an incomplete 74-line version in which the nightingale defends women and the thrush condemns them.",
      "language": "eng",
      "scope": {
        "kind": "whole"
      },
      "evidence_ids": [
